The paper proposes an image steganographic algorithm that uses content transformation between two different domains to hide image messages. This involves the use of a specially trained network to extract transformed images from both domains and use them as public and private keys. The paper also mentions the use of a constrained Cycle-GAN for implementation. Based on these details, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) as the paper deals with image processing and transformation. The second likely sub-category is cryptography (cs.CR) as the paper involves hiding information in an open communication channel. Multimedia (cs.MM) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image steganography. Machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also possible sub-categories as the paper mentions the use of a specially trained network.
